video_title: HEAT at CELTICS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | September 25, 2020
description:
HEAT at CELTICS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | September 25, 2020

The Boston Celtics defeated the Miami Heat, 121-108, in Game 5 of the Eastern Conference Finals. Jayson Tatum (31 PTS, 10 REB, 6 AST) and Jaylen Brown (28 PTS, 8 REB) combined for 59 PTS for the Celtics, while Goran Dragic paced the Heat with 23 PTS. The Miami Heat now lead the best-of-seven series, 3-2.

Game 6: Sunday, September 27 at 7:30pm/et on ESPN
